post.author: bpanjavan
post.title: SharePoint Data View Content Preview
post.content:
This is from a project I worked on recently with two of my colleagues, Zen Lin and Daryl Leachman.

I’m not sure how else to describe this feature / functionality, so I’m calling it the “Data View Content Preview”.  Here’s how it works.  There’s a Data View WebPart on the left side formatted to provide links to the contents of its respective list.  In the middle is the Preview Pane.  When you hover over the items on the Data View WebPart, the Preview Pane (which is really a Content Editor Web Part) shows a preview of the data in the list.

NOTE: The links in your Data View WebPart do NOT have to point directly to the items in the list.  Depending on how you format your XSLT, they can point ANYWHERE.  The focus here is establishing the preview functionality.

First, we start with a custom list:

 

 

This is simply a custom list which contains fields relating to a list of Employees within a company or recruiter database.  The fields vary from single text fields to multi-text fields, to pictures.

The items I’ve put into the list:

 

 

From this list, we now create a Data View WebPart on our main page.  There are multiple ways to do this, but the way I’m most familiar with is through SharePoint Designer.  Here’s a how-to link:

Create a Data View in SharePoint Designer

Obviously, make sure you use your list as the data source, and be sure and include all parameters.

Go to the page itself, and modify the WebPart.  Click on the button to edit the XSL:

 

 

For this particular example, this is what my XSL looked like: 

<xsl:stylesheet xmlns:x=”http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema” xmlns:d=”http://schemas.microsoft.com/sharepoint/dsp” version=”1.0″ exclude-result-prefixes=”xsl msxsl ddwrt” xmlns:ddwrt=”http://schemas.microsoft.com/WebParts/v2/DataView/runtime” xmlns:asp=”http://schemas.microsoft.com/ASPNET/20″ xmlns:__designer=”http://schemas.microsoft.com/WebParts/v2/DataView/designer” xmlns:xsl=”http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform” xmlns:msxsl=”urn:schemas-microsoft-com:xslt” xmlns:SharePoint=”Microsoft.SharePoint.WebControls” xmlns:ddwrt2=”urn:frontpage:internal”>

                        <xsl:output method=”html” indent=”no”/>

                        <xsl:decimal-format NaN=”"/>

                                                                                                                                                <xsl:param name=”dvt_apos”>’</xsl:param>

                                                                                                                                                <xsl:variable name=”dvt_1_automode”>0</xsl:variable>

                                                                                                                                                <xsl:template match=”/”>

                                                                                                                                                                        <xsl:call-template name=”dvt_1″/>

                        </xsl:template>

                                                                                                                                                <xsl:template name=”dvt_1″>

                                                                                                                                                                        <xsl:variable name=”dvt_StyleName”>Table</xsl:variable>

                                                                                                                                                                        <xsl:variable name=”Rows” select=”/dsQueryResponse/Rows/Row”/>

                                                <table border=”0″ width=”100%” cellpadding=”2″ cellspacing=”0″>

                                                                        <tr valign=”top”>

                                                                                                <xsl:if test=”$dvt_1_automode = ‘1′” ddwrt:cf_ignore=”1″>

                                                                                                                        <th class=”ms-vh” width=”1%” nowrap=”nowrap”></th>

                                                                                                </xsl:if>

                                                                                                <th class=”ms-vh” nowrap=”nowrap”>Full Name</th>

                                                                        </tr>

                                                                        <xsl:call-template name=”dvt_1.body”>

                                                                                                <xsl:with-param name=”Rows” select=”$Rows”/>

                                                                        </xsl:call-template>

                                                </table>

                        </xsl:template>

                                                                                                                                                <xsl:template name=”dvt_1.body”>

                                                                                                                                                                        <xsl:param name=”Rows”/>

                                                                                                                                                                        <xsl:for-each select=”$Rows”>

                                                                                                                                                                                                <xsl:call-template name=”dvt_1.rowview”/>

                                                </xsl:for-each>

                        </xsl:template>

                                                                                                                                                <xsl:template name=”dvt_1.rowview”>

                                                <tr>

                                                                        <xsl:if test=”position() mod 2 = 1″>

                                                                                                <xsl:attribute name=”class”>ms-alternating</xsl:attribute>

                                                                        </xsl:if>

                                                                        <xsl:if test=”$dvt_1_automode = ‘1′” ddwrt:cf_ignore=”1″>

                                                                                                <td class=”ms-vb” width=”1%” nowrap=”nowrap”>

                                                                                                                        <span ddwrt:amkeyfield=”ID” ddwrt:amkeyvalue=”ddwrt:EscapeDelims(string(@ID))” ddwrt:ammode=”view”></span>

                                                                                                </td>

                                                                        </xsl:if>

                                                                        <td class=”ms-vb” style=”width:100%;vertical-align:middle;border:solid 1px gray; ”

                                                                                                                        onmousemove=”javascript:return OpenDataPreviewPane(this);”

                                                                                                                        onmouseout=”javascript:return CloseDataPreviewPane(this);”>

                                                                                                                        <a href=”http://litwareserver/Lists/DataViewContentPreviewEmployeeList/DispForm.aspx?ID={@ID}”

                                                                                                                           style=”width:100%; height:30px; vertical-align:middle;”><xsl:value-of select=”@Title”/></a>

                                                                                                                          <span id=”spanDataViewFullName” style=”display:none;”>

                                                                                                                                               <xsl:value-of select=”@Title”/>

                                                                                                                          </span>

                                                                                                                          <span id=”spanDataViewDescription” style=”display:none;”>

                                                                                                                                               <xsl:value-of select=”@Description” disable-output-escaping=”yes”/>

                                                                                                                          </span>

                                                                                                                          <span id=”spanDataViewEmployeePhoto” style=”display:none;”>

                                                                                                                                               <img border=”0″ src=”{substring-before(@PhotoID, ‘, ‘)}” alt=”{substring-after(@PhotoID, ‘, ‘)}”/>

                                                                                                                          </span>

                                                                                                                          <span id=”spanDataViewExperience” style=”display:none;”>

                                                                                                                                               <xsl:value-of select=”@Experience” disable-output-escaping=”yes”/>

                                                                                                                          </span>

                                                                                                                          <span id=”spanDataViewLinks” style=”display:none;”>

                                                                                                                                               <xsl:value-of select=”@Links” disable-output-escaping=”yes”/>

                                                                                                                          </span>

                                                                        </td>

                                                </tr>

                        </xsl:template>

</xsl:stylesheet>

 

I highlighted the most important part, the part that actually displays.  In this table cell, what is displayed for each list item is the Full Name field in a hyper link, pointing toward the list item edit page itself.  REMEMBER, this does not have to point to the list item itself.  It can point anywhere.  In this same cell is a series of HTML <span> elements, all containing the remaining values as if they are to be displayed.  But these are purposely hidden using the CSS style DISPLAY property.  These are here for a reason.

So now we have our Data View WebPart on our page:

  

Now add a Content Editor WebPart to the middle zone of the page.  Here’s the source:

 

<script type=”text/javascript”>

                                                <!–

                                                                        function GetSpanById(listSpans, strID)

                                                                        {

                                                                                                for (var intCounter = 0; intCounter < listSpans.length; intCounter++)

                                                                                                {

                                                                                                                        if (listSpans[intCounter].id == strID)

                                                                                                                                                return listSpans[intCounter];

                                                                                                }

                                                                                                return null;

                                                                        }

                                                                       

                                                                        function OpenDataPreviewPane(sender)

                                                                        {

                                                                                                var tdParent = sender;

                                                                                               

                                                                                                tdParent.className = “ms-itemhover”;

                                                                                               

                                                                                                var listSpans = tdParent.getElementsByTagName(”span”);

                                                                                               

                                                                                                var spanDataViewFullName= GetSpanById(listSpans, “spanDataViewFullName”);

                                                                                                var spanDataViewDescription= GetSpanById(listSpans, “spanDataViewDescription”);

                                                                                                var spanDataViewEmployeePhoto= GetSpanById(listSpans, “spanDataViewEmployeePhoto”);

                                                                                                var spanDataViewExperience= GetSpanById(listSpans, “spanDataViewExperience”);

                                                                                                var spanDataViewLinks= GetSpanById(listSpans, “spanDataViewLinks”);

                                                                                               

                                                                                                var tablePreviewPane = document.getElementById(”tablePreviewPane”);

                                                                                                tablePreviewPane.style.display = “block”;

                                                                                                var spanPreviewPaneFullName = document.getElementById(”spanPreviewPaneFullName”);

                                                                                                spanPreviewPaneFullName.innerHTML = spanDataViewFullName.innerHTML;

                                                                                               

                                                                                                var spanPreviewPaneDescription= document.getElementById(”spanPreviewPaneDescription”);

                                                                                                spanPreviewPaneDescription.innerHTML = spanDataViewDescription.innerHTML;

                                                                                               

                                                                                                var spanPreviewPaneEmployeePhoto= document.getElementById(”spanPreviewPaneEmployeePhoto”);

                                                                                                spanPreviewPaneEmployeePhoto.innerHTML = spanDataViewEmployeePhoto.innerHTML;

                                                                                                                                                                                               

                                                                                                var spanPreviewPaneExperience= document.getElementById(”spanPreviewPaneExperience”);

                                                                                                spanPreviewPaneExperience.innerHTML = spanDataViewExperience.innerHTML;

                                                                                               

                                                                                                var spanPreviewPaneLinks= document.getElementById(”spanPreviewPaneLinks”);

                                                                                                spanPreviewPaneLinks.innerHTML = spanDataViewLinks.innerHTML;

                                                                                               

                                                                                               

                                                                                               

                                                                                               

                                                                                                return false;

                                                                        }

                                                                       

                                                                        function CloseDataPreviewPane(sender)

                                                                        {

                                                                                                var tdParent = sender;

                                                                                                tdParent.className = “ms-vb”;

                                                                                                return false;

                                                                        }

                                                                       

                                                //–>

                        </script>

                        <table id=”tablePreviewPane” class=”ms-vb” style=”display:none;” cellspacing=”0″>

                                                <tr>

                                                                        <td colspan=”2″ >

                                                                                                <span id=”spanPreviewPaneFullName” style=”width:100%; font-size:large; text-align:center;”>

                                                                                               

                                                                                                </span>

                                                                        </td>

                                                </tr>

                                                <tr>

                                                                        <td colspan=”2″>

                                                                                                <span style=”text-decoration:underline;”>Description</span>

                                                                                                <span id=”spanPreviewPaneDescription”>

                                                                                               

                                                                                                </span>

                                                                        </td>

                                                </tr>

                                                <tr>

                                                                        <td style=”width:25%;”>

                                                                                                <span id=”spanPreviewPaneEmployeePhoto”>

                                                                                               

                                                                                                </span>

 

                                                                        </td>

                                                                        <td>

                                                                                                <table style=”width:100%;” class=”ms-vb”>

                                                                                                                        <tr>

                                                                                                                                                <td>

                                                                                                                                                                        <span style=”text-decoration:underline;”>Experience</span>

                                                                                                                                                                        <span id=”spanPreviewPaneExperience”>

                                                                                               

                                                                                                                                                                        </span>

                                                                                                                                                </td>

                                                                                                                        </tr>

                                                                                                                        <tr>

                                                                                                                                                <td>

                                                                                                                                                                        <span style=”text-decoration:underline;”>Links</span>

                                                                                                                                                                        <span id=”spanPreviewPaneLinks”>

                                                                                               

                                                                                                                                                                        </span>

                                                                                                                                                </td>

                                                                                                                        </tr>

                                                                                                </table>

                                                                        </td>

                                                </tr>

                        </table>

  

It’s a little heavy.  So let’s break down what’s going on.  First we’ll focus on the main table that’s displaying the data.  This <table> element, with an id of “tablePreviewPane” holds our preview data.  Essentially its intention is to display the preview data in this format:


 

 

<Full Name>

Description

<Description>

<Employee Photo>

Experience

<Experience>

Links

Links

<Links>

 

Our main JavaScript function, “OpenDataPreviewPane” takes in the table cell element as its sender.  Remember this particular section in our XSL markup:

<td class=”ms-vb” style=”width:100%;vertical-align:middle;border:solid 1px gray; ”

                onmousemove=”javascript:return OpenDataPreviewPane(this);”

                onmouseout=”javascript:return CloseDataPreviewPane(this);”>

 

The “onmousemove” event calls the “OpenDataPreviewPane” function, passing itself as the sender.  The “OpenDataPreviewPane” uses the sender argument to traverse the hidden <span> elements that we left hidden earlier.  One by one, the contents of those elements are grabbed and set to the respective places in the Preview Pane, and the sender, which is the table cell, is highlighted.

 

NOTE: For aesthetics, I set my left WebPart zone to a width of 25%, and my middle WebPart zone to a width of 50%.

 

A couple of questions may arise regarding this implementation:

 

Q: Why didn’t you just use web part connections?

A: We want something not only simple in terms of MOSS features, but RICH.  Dropping Content Editor WebParts onto pages is very simple.

 

Q: Why didn’t you just pass in those parameters as arguments to the JavaScript function?

A: Trying to parse and deal with special characters (ex: single quote) was a nightmare.  This is the entire reason we came up with the “traverse the <span>’s” solution instead.

 

Q: What happens if I change the theme?  Will the color scheme be off?

A: Try it.  The HTML within the Content Editor part uses SharePoint CSS classes so this shouldn’t be a problem

comment.content: This is getting a bit more subjective, but I much prefer the Zune Marketplace. The interface is colorful, has more flair, and some cool features like 'Mixview' that let you quickly see related albums, songs, or other users related to what you're listening to. Clicking on one of those will center on that item, and another set of "neighbors" will come into view, allowing you to navigate around exploring by similar artists, songs, or users. Speaking of users, the Zune "Social" is also great fun, letting you find others with shared tastes and becoming friends with them. You then can listen to a playlist created based on an amalgamation of what all your friends are listening to, which is also enjoyable. Those concerned with privacy will be relieved to know you can prevent the public from seeing your personal listening habits if you so choose.

comment.content: This is getting a bit more subjective, but I much prefer the Zune Marketplace. The interface is colorful, has more flair, and some cool features like 'Mixview' that let you quickly see related albums, songs, or other users related to what you're listening to. Clicking on one of those will center on that item, and another set of "neighbors" will come into view, allowing you to navigate around exploring by similar artists, songs, or users. Speaking of users, the Zune "Social" is also great fun, letting you find others with shared tastes and becoming friends with them. You then can listen to a playlist created based on an amalgamation of what all your friends are listening to, which is also enjoyable. Those concerned with privacy will be relieved to know you can prevent the public from seeing your personal listening habits if you so choose.
